		<h2 class="h2-policy">POLICIES AND PROCEDURES</h2>
	
<p>Our policies and procedures are designed to inform you of your rights on becoming a MGlobal Distributor. We believe it is important that you have easy access to our policies and procedures and take every effort to make sure that they are clearly stated and easily accessible.  This policies and procedures help you to understand the relationship that exists between distributor and company and if you have any concerns regarding the business please refer policies and procedures. The company may amend any part of the contract from time to time as laws and business circumstances change; however, notice of any amendment will be published on our website.</p>
<h4>Definitions</h4>
<ul>
<p>a.	Agreement means the completed online distributor application form which will be submitted to the company.</p>
<p>b.	Application form means form or application dealing the terms and conditions of distributor that is required to be filled and submitted by a person desiring to become company distributor.</p>
<p>c.	Business kit means the literature provided with the distributor Application form.</p>
<p>d.	Company means MGlobal </p>
<p>e.	Compensation Plan means MGlobal  plan as detailed in the appendix.</p>
<p>f.	Individual representative/distributor<br>
Can legal entity be a distributor?</p>
<p>Means a person who is introduced to the  company business and is accepted by the company as a distributor in accordance with policies and procedures; this term includes “sponsor”, except when the context requires otherwise. Distributor are business persons, operating their own businesses, and have no employment, agency or similar relationship with company.</p>
<p>g.	Compensation summary means  the summary of their transactions which will be given to every distributor (by mail /quarterly/weekly)</p>
<p>h.	Identification Number means a unique number given to every distributor by the company when distributor application form is accepted by the company.</p>
<p>i.	Registered office (the company registered address)</p>
<p>j.	Annual renewal date means a date on where distributor was accepted as distributor by the company. Every year the distributor has to renew his distributorship.</p>
<p>k.	Renewal period means a period _____________ of each calendar year during which the distributor is required to renew his distributorship with company</p>
<p>l.	P&P means policies and procedures of “MGlobal  Company”</p>
<p>m.	Services means services rendered by the company or which are available on the Company’s website, company is at its sole discretion to change the services and the packages available on the web site and the same will be intimated to all the distributors.</p>
<p>n.	Sponsor means a distributor who introduces to company an applicant for authorization as a distributor who in turn becomes a distributor by virtue of MGlobal Company’s acceptance of his distribution application.</p>
<p>o.	Upline means distributors above his/her account in the genealogy on case to case basis.</p>
<p>p.	Downline means distributors below his/her account in the genealogy on case to case basis.</p>
</ul>
<p>The purpose of this Privacy Policy is to inform you as to what information may be collected from you when you visit our website (“the Site”) or when you become a Distributor, how such information will be used by Company and/or other persons or entities, with whom such information may be shared, use and distribution of such information, your ability to edit, update, correct or delete such information and the security procedures that we have implemented to protect your privacy.</p>
<h4>Independent Representatives/Distributor</h4>
<p>1.	An applicant to become a Distributor must fill up the form available on the website “APPLICATION/DISTRIBUTOR FORM”, and by filling up the form and by submitting form through online the distributor has agreed to all the terms and conditions set forth in policies and procedures.</p>

<p>1.2	To become a Distributor/representatives:</p>
<ul>
<p>a.	Must have attained legal age in the state, territory or country of your domicile.</p>
<p>b.	Must complete Application form and application form has been received and accepted by the company.</p>
<p>c.	Must have an identity card/proof of residency, work autorisations, and ability to legally conduct business in the country.</p>
<p>d.	Must be of a sound mind</p>
<p>e.	Must have a sponsoring upline</p>
<p>f.	Must be able to read and understand the terms and conditions.</p>
<p>g.	Must not have been suspended from his current profession or business by professional association, society, or institution</p>
<p>h.	Must not be in jail and or confined to any correctional institution of any kind.</p>
</ul>
<p>1.3	The opportunity to become a distributor is available to anyone regardless of race, sex, nationality, religious or political beliefs. </p>

<h4>2.	Acceptance of the form</h4>
<p>The company reserves the right to accept or reject any application to be a distributor and the company is not bound to state the reasons for rejecting the application.</p>
<p>An application shall be considered accepted when MGlobal  enters the personal details of a distributor on its records and communicates its acceptance to distributor in any manner whatsoever whether by issuance of an Identification Card or by sending an email.</p>
<p>The distributor shall not impose any conditions for the prospective sponsor/distributor the only requirement for becoming a distributor would be filling up the application form.</p>
<h4>3.	Identification number</h4>
<p>Every distributor will be issued a unique personal identification number, which will be used by the distributor for security purposes when placing services/products orders and when requesting genealogy and status information.</p>
<h4>4.	TERM</h4>
<p>The contract is valid for a period of one (1) year from the date of sign up. Each year the distributorship have to be renewed. The company will charge nominal fees for renewal of their distributorship. The distributor is free to use their reward points for renewal of their membership/distributorship.</p>
<p>5.	RESPONSIBILITIES OF ALL Distributors/ representatives</p>
<p>5.1.	At all times, Distributors must adhere strictly to the guidelines, policies and procedures, terms & conditions, compensation plan/reward plan mentioned in the literature accompanying the company, and any amendment thereto affected by the company from time to time, will be published in the website or any other means of communication prior to their going into effect.</p>
	<p>Once a distributor application and agreement has been accepted by company the benefits of compensation plan and distributor agreement are available to the new distributor. These benefits include the right to:</p>
<ul>
<p>a.	Sell company products and services</p>
<p>b.	Participate in compensation plan (receive bonuses and commission, if eligible)</p>
<p>c.	Sponsor other individuals as distributors into the company business and thereby a marketing organization and progress through the company compensation plan</p>
<p>d.	Receive periodic literature and communications</p>
<p>e.	Participate in company sponsored support, service, training, motivational and recognition functions upon payment of appropriate charges, if applicable, and 
In the event a sponsor ceases to be qualified distributor, the rights of the distributors whom he/she may have sponsored shall pass up to the next qualified distributor in his/her line of sponsorship.</p>
</ul>
<p>5.2	Right to sponsor</p>
<p>The distributor understands that he/she is not compensated for sponsoring other representatives/customer but earns (rewards/compensation) solely on the sale of products and/ or services to ultimate consumers.</p>
<p>5.3	Fictitious /assumed names</p>
<p>A person shall not apply as a distributor using fictitious name or assumed name. 	 Must comply with all federal, state and local statutes, regulations and ordinances concerning the operation of their business.</p>
<p>5.4	No right to represent company.</p>
<p>MGlobal distributors are distributors operating their own business and are not franchisees, joint venture partners, employees/agents of company or its affiliated companies.</p>
<p>A distributor has a no right to negotiate or conclude any contract on behalf of the company. Nor shall he/she hold himself/herself out as having such right. He/she shall not represent himself/herself as agent, representative or employee of the company.</p>
<p>A Company is not liable for distributor for the payment or copayment of any employee benefits. Distributors set their own hours and determine how to conduct their business. </p>
<p>A Distributor is an independent contractor and is responsible for his or her own business expenses, decisions, and actions.</p>


<h4>6	Non-exclusivity right</h4>
<p>A distributor has a nonexclusive right to market and promote products/services of the company. There are no geographical limitations on sponsoring or selling country; provided however, that the company reserves the right not to sell services in any states, territories or countries.</p>
<p>The distributor have no territorial limits. The distributors are free to operate anywhere within the territory .</p>
<h4>7	Cross lining:</h4>
<ul>
<p>a.	No distributor may sponsor or attempt to sponsor another distributor from different line of sponsorship to “switch” to another line of sponsorship.</p>
<p>b.	No distributor shall engage in cross lining. In order to be eligible for the various monetary and nonmonetary benefits available through the MGlobal sales and marketing plan,</p>
<p>c.	No distributor must, directly or indirectly, induce/entice other MGlobal distributors to change their line of sponsorship.</p>
<p>d.	Under no circumstances, direct or indirect, nor for purpose of helping another person, shall a distributor solicit, interfere or attempt to induce another distributor to leave his line of sponsorship or change his line of sponsorship.</p>
</ul>

<h4>8.	Non-compete clause</h4>
<p>Subject to the provisions of this Section, a Distributor is prohibited, during the term of the Contract, from building a business, directly or indirectly, as an distributor, employee, executive, or consultant to or on behalf of a Competing Company.  This Section does not apply to a Distributor if, prior to becoming a Distributor with the Company or prior to the effective date of this policy, he or she was acting as an distributor, employee, executive, or consultant to or on behalf of a Competing Company.</p>
<h4>9.	Obligation of not referring to other programmes</h4>
<p>A distributor shall not sponsor or attempt to sponsor or knowingly assist another person to sponsor another distributor’s sales organization.  </p>
<h4>10.	Breach of security</h4>
<p>All distributors have a responsibility to maintain network integrity of the company. Any distributors who is found attempted “hacking” into or interfering of the company’s database or any part of the Company’s computer system (hardware and/or software) or attempting to do any aforesaid acts without the proper authorization shall be liable to immediate termination of his distributorship. They shall also be liable for all consequential damages and losses of the company.</p>
<h4>11.	Legal compliance</h4>
<p>Distributors must comply with all laws, statutes, regulations and ordinances concerning the operation of their business.</p>
<h4>12.	Tax expenditures etc.,</h4>
<p>Distributor are personally responsible for paying income taxes on any income they generate as distributor. Unless required by laws, regulations, or rules, the Company shall have no obligation to provide tax information about the commissions of the distributor.</p>
<p>The commissions are paid by the Company after deducting all statutory deductions.  If subsequent to payment of commissions, the Company is found liable for not deducting taxes relating to those commissions and/or bonuses, in that event the distributor shall indemnify the Company for such a liability.</p>

<h4>13.	Obligation to the company</h4>
<p>A distributor shall, at all times remain loyal to the company and shall not publish any written /verbal disparaging or adverse information/statement against the company. He shall hold the company’s management in high esteem at all times, failing which, he may be terminated notwithstanding that he may be liable for libel and slander.</p>
<h4>14.	Unauthorized Claims and Actions</h4>
<p>A Distributor is fully responsible for all of his or her verbal and written statements made regarding services/products, and the Marketing and Compensation Plan which are not expressly contained in official company materials/business kit. Distributors agree to indemnify MGlobal and _____s’ directors, officers, employees, and agents, and hold them harmless from any and all liability including judgments, civil penalties, refunds, and attorney fees, court costs, incurred by company as a result of the Distributor’s unauthorized representations or actions. This provision shall survive even after the termination of the Distributor Agreement.</p>
<ul>
<h4>a.	Service Claims</h4>
<p>No false promises:</p>
<p>No Distributor shall make any offer to sell any company services/products which is not accurate and truthful as to price, quality, performance and availability of services provided by company.</p>
<p>No distributor shall knowingly submit false or misleading information about the company or company products/services.</p>
<p>No distributor shall not make exaggerated service/product claims or non-guarantee claims with regard to services distributed by the company.</p>
<p>No distributors shall do anything detrimental to the reputation and image of the company, its products, distributors, trademarks or names.</p>
<p>No distributor shall not pass of any other services in a fraudulent manner as if the services are distributed by the company. (Passing off)</p>
<p>No distributor shall engage in any deceptive or unlawful trade practice. A deceptive or unlawful trade practice is one, which been defined as such by any central, state, or local law or regulation.</p>
<p>A company distributor shall at all times conduct himself or herself in a courteous and considerate manner and shall not engage in any high-pressure selling, but shall make a fair presentation of MGlobal  services including, with appropriate, demonstrations of such services.</p>
</ul>
<ul>
<h4>b.	Income Claims</h4>
<p>In their enthusiasm to enroll prospective Distributors, some Distributors are occasionally tempted to make income claims or earnings representations to demonstrate the inherent power of direct selling or network marketing. This is counterproductive because new Distributors may become disappointed very quickly if their results are not as extensive or as rapid as the results others have achieved. Therefore, Distributors may not misrepresent the actual or potential sales or earnings of their Distributorship. Any earnings or sales representations made by a Distributor shall be based upon documented information, in compliance with applicable government laws /ordinances and Direct Selling Association regulations.</p>
</ul>

<h4>15.	Right of sponsorship</h4>
<ul>
<p>a.	Distributor should provide all distributors him /her with unaltered/ complete business kit.</p>
<p>b.	Distributor abide by code of ethics and policies and procedures in its true spirit.</p>
<p>c.	Distributor train and motivate all distributors to follow the company terms & conditions, policies and procedures, code of ethics.</p>
</ul>

<h4>16.	Obligations to downlines</h4>
<p>Any distributor who introduces another distributor to the company is highly recommended to perform a bonafide assistance and training function to ensure that his downline is properly operating and conducting his distributor business. It is both to the advantages of sponsor uplines and their downlines to have ongoing contact and communication.</p>

<h4>17.	Placement	</h4>
<p>Once an Applicant’s distributor agreement is accepted by the company, the new distributor is placed in the sponsors down line organization. A sponsor may place the new distributor on his or her first level or anywhere else in the sponsor’s down line organization. A sponsor may not place a new distributor outside its downline organization. If this occurs, the company retains the right to make adjustments to the organization to allow for correct payout and to ensure that all lines are complete.</p>
<h4>18.	Refund policy </h4>
<p>The company services have 7-Day Money –Back guarantee for the retail customer. The 7 day commences on the date the customer receives the services. When a customer requests the guarantee be honored, the distributor must respond quickly and courteously. He may offer the customer a choice of a full refund of the purchase price or full credit for exchange of other services in accordance with the return procedures.</p>
<p>Company ensure that customer refund policy is thoroughly and properly understood and applied, and to interview in any disputes between customers and distributors to assure they are settled promptly and amicable.</p>
<p>Company will honor refund policies provided by any governmental law applicable to distributor.</p>
<h4>19.	RENEWAL</h4>
<p>In order to remain a Distributor/client of the company services, beyond the membership period a Distributor must annually renew his or her company MGlobal  during the renewal period.</p>
<h4>20.	COMMISSIONS AND BONUSES /REWARDS</h4>
<p>Company will pay Sales Representative/distributor commissions and bonuses on orders received and accepted for sale of services to the ultimate consumer as per the terms and conditions set forth in the compensation plan.</p>
<p>Distributors must adhere company’s compensation plan, terms and conditions, official literature and also and also must comply with the terms of the company as set forth in official company’s literature. </p>

<h4>21.	Resignations and termination</h4>
<ul>
<h4>a.	Resignation</h4>
<p>A distributor may resign their distributorship for any reason at any time, by submitting a email .</p>
<p>The resignation becomes effective when received, validated, and accepted by the company. Company will intimate the distributor with regard to acceptance of his/her resignation. If the company does not receive hard copy of the resignation letter or the conditions are not met, then distributor is still deemed to be a distributor.</p>
<p>The hard copy……letter needs to be sent to the official address_________email</p>
<h4>b.	Termination</h4>
<p>Company reserves the right to terminate or delete a distributorship at any time with or without giving prior notice whenever company deems that this is necessary and appropriate action to be taken against the distributor.</p>
<p>Termination means the complete cancellation of distributorship and revocation of distributor’s right to conduct the company business. This includes cancellation of their right to receive any further income from the distributorship whether accruing before or after the termination date. The termination is effective on the date indicated in the written notification from company to the distributor.</p>
<p>If a distributor wishes to ask the Company to review the decision of termination, he/she shall make such a request to the Company in writing within fifteen (15) days from the date of notice of termination. If no such request is received by the Company within the fifteen (15) day period, the termination will automatically be deemed final. If a Distributor files a timely written request, the Company will review the decision and notify the Distributor of the result of the review within thirty (30) days after receipt of the Distributor's request. Thereafter, the Company will not further review its decision. In the event the termination decision is not reversed, the termination will remain effective as of the date stated in the original termination notice. </p>
<p>Upon the termination or deletion of a distributorship for any cause pursuant to these rules, the distributor will have no claim against company as a result of the termination or deletion. </p>
</ul>
<h4>22.Confidential Information </h4>
<p>During the term of the Agreement, the Company may supply to Distributors confidential information, including, but not limited to genealogical and Downline reports, Customer lists, Customer information developed by the Company or developed for and on behalf of the Company by Distributors (including, but not limited to, credit data, Customer and Distributor profiles and product purchase information), Distributor lists, manufacturer and supplier information, business reports, commission or sales reports and such other financial and business information which the Company may designate as confidential. All such information (whether in written or electronic format) is proprietary and confidential to the Company and is transmitted to Distributors in strictest confidence on a “need to know” basis for use solely in the Distributors business with the Company. Distributors must use their best efforts to keep such information confidential and must not disclose any such information to any third party, or use such information for any non-Company activity directly or indirectly while a Distributor and thereafter. Distributors must not use the information to compete with the Company or for any purpose other than promoting the Company's program and its products and services. Upon determination, non-renewal or termination of the Agreement, Distributors must discontinue the use of such confidential information and promptly return any confidential information in their possession to the Company. </p>

<p>The company trade name, trademarks, and service marks are important and valuable business assets. They help identify the source and reputation of the company business, products, and services.</p>

<p>Trade mark must be protected from misuse and infringement by others, or they can be lost. The company makes every possible effort to protect the trademark, logo’s etc., if any person improperly uses the trademark/logo the value and importance can be greatly diminished. The company will not allow to use its trademark/logo, symbol etc., without prior permission. Company will issue cease-and desist orders to any persons using its trade name, mark, designs, and symbols without its permission and will if necessary follow appropriate court action for failure to comply with cease –and-desist order.  </p>

<h4>23.Copyrighted materials: </h4>
<p>All company printed material is copyrighted and may not be reproduced in whole or in part by the distributor or other persons except by written permission from company.</p>
<p>Spamming and Unsolicited Faxes</p>
<p>Company does not permit distributors to send unsolicited commercial emails unless such emails strictly comply with applicable laws and regulations.
<p>Identification</p>
<p>All Distributors and co-applicants are required to provide correct identification and tax information upon the request of the Company.  Failure to provide this information when requested could result in suspension or termination of the Distributorship.</p>
<p>Income Taxes</p>
<p>Each Distributor is responsible for paying local, state/provincial and federal taxes on any income generated as an Distributor.  ______ Company will provide the commission statement to distributors upon submission of a written request per distributorship.</p>
</ul>

<h4>24.GENERAL PROVISIONS</h4>
<ul>
<h4>a.	Force majeure</h4>
<p>Company shall not be responsible for acts beyond its control, including but, not limited to: fire, flood, earthquake, storms, power outages, labor difficulty, equipment failure, supplier problems, or other difficulties that might prevent performance according to this agreement.</p>
<h4>b.	Amendments</h4>
<p>The company reserves the right to amend and change/the p&p, its prices, services availability and/or the compensation plan at any time without prior notice as it deems appropriate. Amendments will be communicated to distributors through official company, publications or company website___________________.  </p>
<h4>c.	Entire agreement</h4>
<p>The agreement, the p&p and compensation plan together constitute the entire agreement of between distributor and the company.</p>
<h4>d.	Severability</h4>
<p>If at any time any provision of the agreement /and p&p is or becomes illegal, invalid, or unenforceable in any respect under the law of any jurisdiction, neither the legality, validity or enforceability of the remaining provisions of the agreement and/ or p&p under the law of that or any other jurisdiction, nor the legality, validity or enforceability of such provision under the law of any other jurisdiction shall in any way be affected or impaired thereby. </p>
</ul>

<h4>25.Grievances and complaints</h4>
<p>Where distributor has a grievance or complaint with another Distributor(s) regarding any practice or conduct in relationship to their respective company (name) businesses, the complaining Distributor(s) should first discuss the problem with the other Distributor(s). If this does not resolve the problem, the complaining Distributor(s) should report the problem to his/her upline to resolve the issue at a local level. If the matter cannot be resolved within thirty (30) days from the date on which it was reported to the upline , it must be reported in writing to the company  Compliance Department. The Compliance Department will review the complaint and make a final decision. The complaint should identify specific instances of alleged improper conduct and, to the extent possible, identify the relevant dates on which the event(s) complained of took place, the location(s) where they occurred, and all persons who have firsthand knowledge of the improper conduct.</p>
<ul>
<h4>Compliance department review</h4>
<p>Upon receipt of a written complaint, the Company Compliance Department will investigate the matter, review the applicable policies, and render a decision on how the dispute shall be resolved. The Compliance Department may also issue disciplinary sanctions consistent with the provisions of Subject to applicable law, Company Compliance Department’s decision shall be final and binding on the Distributors to the dispute.</p>
<h4>Disciplinary actions</h4>
<p>Violations of any of the terms and conditions of the Distributor(s) Agreement or these Policies and Procedures, or any illegal, fraudulent, deceptive, or unethical business conduct by an  Distributor(s), may result, at company ‘s discretion, in one or more of the following sanctions:</p>
<ul>
<p>a.	A written warning, clarifying the meaning and application of a specific policy or procedure, and advising that a continued breach will result in further sanctions;</p>
<p>b.	Probation, which may include requiring an Distributor (s) to take remedial action and will include follow-up monitoring by Company to ensure compliance with the Agreement;</p>
<p>c.	Withdrawal or denial of an award or recognition, or restricting participation in COMPANY sponsored events for a specified period of time or until the Distributor(s) satisfies certain specified condition:</p>
<p>d.	Suspension of certain privileges of Distributor(s)ship, including but not limited to placing a product order, participating in COMPANY programs, progressing in the Business Plan, or participating as a Sponsor, for a specified period of time or until the Distributor(s) satisfies certain specified conditions or any other right or privilege;</p>
<p>e.	Withholding commissions or payouts for a specified period of time or until the Distributor(s) satisfies certain specified conditions;</p>
<p>f.	Imposing fair and reasonable fines or other penalties in proportion to actual damages incurred by COMPANY and as permitted by law; and/or </p>
<p>g.	Terminating the Distributor(s)ship by terminating the Distributor Agreement.</p>
</ul>
</ul>
